      "step_id": "83f97d9f",
      "step_index": 2,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "### Key motifs / functional groups\n- **Bicyclic heteroaromatic core:** a **dimethoxy-substituted fused aza-heteroaromatic** (looks like a quinazoline-like scaffold: multiple ring nitrogens, planar aromatic system).\n- **Two methoxy groups (\u2013OCH\u2083)** on the aromatic core \u2192 add lipophilicity and maintain aromatic character.\n- **Tertiary amine in a saturated ring:** **N-substituted piperazine-like ring** (`N3CCN(... )CC3`) with:\n  - One ring nitrogen **substituted by an amide** (so that N is **not basic**).\n  - The other ring nitrogen **attached to the heteroaromatic core** (this N is **basic** and likely protonated at pH 7.4).\n- **Amide linkage:** `N(C(=O)...)` \u2192 H-bond acceptor; reduces basicity at that nitrogen; adds polarity.\n- **Furan ring** (`c4ccco4`) as the amide substituent \u2192 aromatic/hydrophobic domain, but smaller/less hydrophobic than phenyl.",
      "tool_name": null,
      "tool_input": null,
      "tool_output": null,
      "timestamp": "2026-02-26T19:57:39.550082+00:00"
    },
    {
      "step_id": "1f33b9e9",
      "step_index": 3,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "### Structural alerts relevant to hERG\n- **Cationic center + aromatic domains**: present (one protonatable amine + multiple aromatic rings).\n- **\u201cTerfenadine-like\u201d long, highly lipophilic, flexible motif**: **not present** (this molecule is more compact and heteroatom-rich).\n- **Piperidine/piperazine + aromatic**: **partially present** (piperazine-like + aromatics), which is a common hERG-enabling pattern.",
      "tool_name": null,
